<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>Inline: Background rendering test</title>
        <style type="text/css">
            * { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
            body {
                width: 800px;
                height: 600px;
                padding: 20px;
                background: #f5f5f5;
                font-family: sans-serif;
                font-size: 16px;
            }
            .container {
                background: white;
                padding: 20px;
                border: 2px solid #333;
            }
            .inline-bg {
                display: inline;
                background: #e74c3c;
                color: white;
                padding: 5px 10px;
            }
            .inline-bg-2 {
                display: inline;
                background: #3498db;
                color: white;
                padding: 5px 10px;
            }
            .inline-bg-3 {
                display: inline;
                background: #2ecc71;
                color: white;
                padding: 5px 10px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            <p>This is normal text with <span class="inline-bg">inline red background</span> and more text.</p>
            <p>Another line with <span class="inline-bg-2">inline blue background</span> in the middle.</p>
            <p>Mixed: <span class="inline-bg">red</span> then <span class="inline-bg-2">blue</span> then <span class="inline-bg-3">green</span> inline elements.</p>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
